To get past a "Please Wait" screen on a remote machine, you can restart the Remote Desktop Services or kill the RDP-related processes using commands like taskkill /IM rdpclip.exe /F and taskkill /IM mstsc.exe /F. This often resolves the issue without needing to reboot the entire machine.

[https://external-content.duckduckgo.com/ip3/insomnyak.medium.com.ico] Medium<https://insomnyak.medium.com/no-restart-needed-fixing-the-dreaded-please-wait-for-remote-desktop-connections-3868785cf36>[https://external-content.duckduckgo.com/ip3/tsplus.net.ico] tsplus.net<https://tsplus.net/remote-desktop-stuck-on-please-wait/>
Troubleshooting the "Please Wait" Screen

When encountering a "Please Wait" screen while trying to connect to a remote machine, there are several methods to resolve the issue without rebooting the entire system.

Restart Remote Desktop Services
* Access the Remote Machine: Use an SSH client to connect to the remote machine.
* Restart Services: Execute the following commands to restart the Remote Desktop Services:
* net stop TermService
* net start TermService
Kill RDP-Related Processes

If restarting the services does not work, you can terminate specific processes that may be causing the hang:

Command Description
taskkill /IM rdpclip.exe /F Forcefully stops the clipboard redirection utility.
taskkill /IM mstsc.exe /F Forcefully stops the Remote Desktop client.
Combined Command for Efficiency

To streamline the process, you can use a combined command that executes multiple actions in one go:

bash

(taskkill /IM rdpclip.exe /F /T || echo rdpclip.exe not running) && (taskkill /IM mstsc.exe /F /T || echo mstsc.exe not running) && net stop TermService && net start TermService

This command will attempt to kill the processes and restart the services, providing feedback if any process is not running.

Additional Tips
* Ensure you have administrative privileges on the remote machine.
* If the issue persists, consider restarting the remote machine as a last resort, as it may resolve underlying issues causing the hang.







